{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":12933,"name":"n9.","username":"n91","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/9de053/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-07-22T15:28:19.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWhen I am rendering scene to texture and displaying only UI elements, screen doesn‚Äôt seem to be cleared:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://i.imgur.com/p6NCHft.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"271\" height=\"160\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe simplified code (in C# via UrhoSharp) producing this is following:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003e        Text helloText;\n\n        protected override void Start()\n        {\n            helloText = new Text();\n            helloText.SetFont(font: ResourceCache.GetFont(\"Fonts/Font.ttf\"), size: 15);\n            UI.Root.AddChild(helloText);\n\n            var scene = new Scene();\n            scene.CreateComponent\u0026lt;Octree\u0026gt;();\n\n            var camera = scene.CreateChild(\"camera\").CreateComponent\u0026lt;Camera\u0026gt;();\n\n            var tx = new Texture2D();\n            tx.SetSize(10, 10, Graphics.RGBFormat, TextureUsage.Rendertarget);\n\n            var rs = tx.RenderSurface;\n            rs.UpdateMode = RenderSurfaceUpdateMode.Updatealways;\n            rs.SetViewport(0, new Viewport(scene, camera, null));\n        }\n\n        protected override void OnUpdate(float timeStep)\n        {\n            helloText.Value = ((char)(DateTime.Now.Second % 4 + 'A')).ToString();\n        }\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHowever when I the render surface part. The output is what I want:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"http://i.imgur.com/3epPv8U.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"271\" height=\"160\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhat I am doing wrong? Is it a feature/bug of UrhoSharp/Urho3d?\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:13:22.486Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":47,"reads":4,"readers_count":3,"score":235.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":2134,"topic_slug":"screen-not-cleared-when-using-ui-with-rendersurface","display_username":"n9.","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":504,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12934,"name":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","username":"cadaver","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/cadaver/{size}/3_2.png","created_at":"2016-07-22T16:50:35.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThis is a bug, or rather an unhandled situation. The Renderer checks if there are no views, and in that case it clears the screen each frame, instead of relying on the views overwriting the screen contents. However in this case there are views, though not backbuffer views. So it really should be checking that there is at least one active view that renders to the backbuffer, and if not, clear the screen.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:13:22.574Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":3,"readers_count":2,"score":0.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":2134,"topic_slug":"screen-not-cleared-when-using-ui-with-rendersurface","display_username":"Lasse √ñ√∂rni","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"Urho3D Author","title_is_group":false,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":true,"staff":true,"us